cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

This paper examines partisan differences in behavior, communication patterns, and social interactions of politically-active Twitter users, which falls under the scope of social media analysis and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to classify users based on their political affiliation, which could also fit under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also analyzes the network structure of the communication activity, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks).
